      "retweeted_tweet_id": null,
      "text": "This is a huge day for Birmingham, our great state, and the U.S. Coast Guard.\n\nThis exciting announcement further positions Alabama as a national leader in supporting our incredible U.S. Armed Forces and law enforcement personnel.\n\nAlabama stands as a proud leader in military excellence, and we’re honored to host this new training center that will help mold the next generation of Coast Guard members.\n\nThank you to @POTUS, @Sec_Noem, and Admiral Lunday for making a tremendous decision that will strengthen our homeland security long into the future.\n\nMy full statement here: https://t.co/FmCxaxzznV",
      "text_resolved": "This is a huge day for Birmingham, our great state, and the U.S. Coast Guard.\n\nThis exciting announcement further positions Alabama as a national leader in supporting our incredible U.S. Armed Forces and law enforcement personnel.\n\nAlabama stands as a proud leader in military excellence, and we’re honored to host this new training center that will help mold the next generation of Coast Guard members.\n\nThank you to @POTUS, @Sec_Noem, and Admiral Lunday for making a tremendous decision that will strengthen our homeland security long into the future.\n\nMy full statement here: https://www.britt.senate.gov/news/press-releases/u-s-coast-guard-selects-birmingham-southern-college-campus-for-new-training-center/",
